HEADWORD: Li
<hw>Li</hw> <pr>(l⟦emac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A Chinese
measure of distance, being a little more than one third of a
mile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A Chinese copper coin; a cash. See
<er>Cash</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Liability</ent>⟦br⟧
